Saudi Energy Minister Khalid Al-Falih met with Nigerian President Muhammadu Buhari to discuss cooperation between the two OPEC member countries in the energy sector, the minister said in a tweet on Saturday.   Al-Falih said that he met with President Buhari on the margins of the World Economic Forum on the Middle East and North Africa in Jordan, where they discussed “ways of cooperating in the fields of energy and industry, and the importance of cooperation for the stability of the global oil market.”